      <div class="card">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>The bot isn't responding to my markdown files</h4>
          <p>Make sure the bot is invited to the channel where you're uploading files. Type <code>@Markdown Viewer</code> in the channel and invite the bot when prompted.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>My rendered link shows "Not Found"</h4>
          <p>Rendered files are automatically deleted after 24 hours. Please re-upload your markdown file to generate a new link.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>Can I use this in private channels?</h4>
          <p>Yes! Just invite the bot to your private channel. The bot only has access to channels where it's explicitly invited.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>How do I uninstall the app?</h4>
          <p>Go to your Slack workspace settings > Manage apps > Find "Markdown Viewer" > Remove. All associated data will be deleted immediately.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>Is my data secure?</h4>
          <p>Yes. We only process markdown files temporarily, use HTTPS encryption, and automatically delete all content after 24 hours. See our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for details.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h4>Does the app support Mermaid diagrams?</h4>
          <p>Yes! Mermaid diagram syntax in your markdown files will be automatically rendered as interactive diagrams.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

